      <h2>About Nicole</h2>
      <p>I hold a doctorate in Psychotherapy Science from Vienna and am a certified Integrative Gestalt psychotherapist practising in Singapore. Before entering psychotherapy, I trained as a biochemist at the National University of Singapore and built a career in the food and beverage industry.</p>
      <p>My path into mental health deepened during the refugee crisis in Austria, where I worked with asylum seekers and war trauma survivors across language and cultural divides. That experience — of sitting with suffering that had no shared language — shaped everything I now write and practise.</p>
      <p>I am also a painter. I grew up in a multicultural Chinese-Eurasian family, attended a convent school, and carry an outsider's perspective on Western therapeutic culture that informs much of what I do. I maintain a full clinical practice alongside my writing, art, and community.</p>
